2023-09-09T18:28:25Z	Make a prototype for #Lists for twtxt/yarn on: http://darch.dk/twtxt-lists  ![](https://neotxt.dk/media/E5Tantd3jL2oNewVNGCCLh.png)  It is based on [twtxt-php](https://github.com/eapl-gemugami/twtxt-php) by @eapl.mx, which is based on my own [phpub2twtxt](https://github.com/sorenpeter/phpub2twtxt)
2023-09-09T20:46:06Z	(#jvs2zmq) @<mckinley https://twtxt.net/user/mckinley/twtxt.txt> not sure I follow?  There is not metadata extension for lists just yet, but my idea is to have lines like this in your main twtxt.txt: `# list = Name of List https://darch.dk/twtxt-lists/twtxt-feeds_by_me.txt`.  Each list-file is then just simply as list of feeds like this: `# follow = darch https://neotxt.dk/user/darch/twtxt.txt`
2023-09-11T07:54:24Z	(#jvs2zmq) @<mckinley https://twtxt.net/user/mckinley/twtxt.txt> My idea is that lists can be both private and public, so you can share as list of curated feeds on a specific topic with others and also have a private list of feeds you don't want the world to know that you are reading. Making it work as a public format first was the easiest to do on top of twtxt-php.
